<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,272,151,177]" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">Head:</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[366,454,151,177]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="13" pageNumber="512" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[537,627,151,177]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="13" pageNumber="512" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
; brown (
<figureCitation box="[725,809,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,183,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[157,1429,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 68–74. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 68. Dorsal view; 69. Abdomen ventral view; 70. Posterior margins of terga; 71. Labrum; 72. Hypopharynx; 73. Left mandible; 74. Right mandible." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042544/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
); subquadrangular; anterior and lateral margins convex, with rows of dense hair-like setae directed medially-dorsally-backward and pressed to head; posterior margin slightly concave. Compound eyes grayish black. Antennal scape, pedicels and flagellum brown. Labrum wide, dark brown, anterior margin with 14–15 denticles; long hair-like setae laterally (
<figureCitation box="[910,993,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,183,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[157,1429,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 68–74. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 68. Dorsal view; 69. Abdomen ventral view; 70. Posterior margins of terga; 71. Labrum; 72. Hypopharynx; 73. Left mandible; 74. Right mandible." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042544/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">Fig. 71</figureCitation>
). Hypopharynx as in 
<figureCitation box="[1235,1318,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,183,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[157,1429,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 68–74. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 68. Dorsal view; 69. Abdomen ventral view; 70. Posterior margins of terga; 71. Labrum; 72. Hypopharynx; 73. Left mandible; 74. Right mandible." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042544/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">Fig. 72</figureCitation>
. Mandible with scattered setae along molar area; incisors well developed; outer incisor longer than inner incisor (
<figureCitation box="[1293,1424,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,183,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[157,1429,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 68–74. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 68. Dorsal view; 69. Abdomen ventral view; 70. Posterior margins of terga; 71. Labrum; 72. Hypopharynx; 73. Left mandible; 74. Right mandible." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042544/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">Figs 73–74</figureCitation>
). Maxilla as in 
<figureCitation box="[300,381,330,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 75–84" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,744,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-274@13.[151,1436,741,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 75–84. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 75. Maxilla; 76. Labium; 77. Dorsal surface of femur; 78. Foreleg; 79. Midleg; 80. Hindleg; 81. Claw; 82. Gill I; 83. Gill III; 84. Gill VII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042548/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">Fig. 75</figureCitation>
. Labium broad, glossae with V-shaped separation, subtriangular; paraglossae slightly expanded laterally; apical segment of palp acutely pointed, dorsal surface with dense row of comb setae (
<figureCitation box="[1215,1300,367,394]" captionStart="FIGURES 75–84" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,744,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-274@13.[151,1436,741,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 75–84. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 75. Maxilla; 76. Labium; 77. Dorsal surface of femur; 78. Foreleg; 79. Midleg; 80. Hindleg; 81. Claw; 82. Gill I; 83. Gill III; 84. Gill VII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042548/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">Fig. 76</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,297,403,429]" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">Thorax:</emphasis>
Pronotum pale brown; mesonotum darker brown with paramedian pair of darker spots anteriorly and pair of lateroparapsidal sutures curved inside posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[799,883,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,183,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[157,1429,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 68–74. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 68. Dorsal view; 69. Abdomen ventral view; 70. Posterior margins of terga; 71. Labrum; 72. Hypopharynx; 73. Left mandible; 74. Right mandible." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042544/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
). Legs (
<figureCitation box="[972,1105,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 75–84" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,744,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-274@13.[151,1436,741,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 75–84. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 75. Maxilla; 76. Labium; 77. Dorsal surface of femur; 78. Foreleg; 79. Midleg; 80. Hindleg; 81. Claw; 82. Gill I; 83. Gill III; 84. Gill VII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042548/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">Figs 78–80</figureCitation>
): Femora brown; hypodermal spot on dorsal surface; dense row of long setae on outer margin; scattered stout setae on dorsal surface (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1423,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 75–84" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,744,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-274@13.[151,1436,741,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 75–84. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 75. Maxilla; 76. Labium; 77. Dorsal surface of femur; 78. Foreleg; 79. Midleg; 80. Hindleg; 81. Claw; 82. Gill I; 83. Gill III; 84. Gill VII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042548/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
); margin of tibia with dense hair-like setae. Claw with 5 denticles (
<figureCitation box="[882,965,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 75–84" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,744,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-274@13.[151,1436,741,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 75–84. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 75. Maxilla; 76. Labium; 77. Dorsal surface of femur; 78. Foreleg; 79. Midleg; 80. Hindleg; 81. Claw; 82. Gill I; 83. Gill III; 84. Gill VII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042548/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,546,572]" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Abdominal terga brown, a row of spines on posterior margin of segment I–X, terga III–VIII with a pair of brown spots (
<figureCitation box="[409,542,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,183,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[157,1429,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 68–74. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 68. Dorsal view; 69. Abdomen ventral view; 70. Posterior margins of terga; 71. Labrum; 72. Hypopharynx; 73. Left mandible; 74. Right mandible." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042544/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">Figs 68, 70</figureCitation>
); posterior margin of terga with rather short spines; segments II–VII with long posterolateral extensions; sterna pale with pair of brown color marking on each segments (
<figureCitation box="[1153,1237,619,646]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,183,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[157,1429,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 68–74. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 68. Dorsal view; 69. Abdomen ventral view; 70. Posterior margins of terga; 71. Labrum; 72. Hypopharynx; 73. Left mandible; 74. Right mandible." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042544/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
). Gill I elongated, somewhat extended beneath of abdomen, middle pairs large widely rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1023,1107,655,682]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,183,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[157,1429,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 68–74. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 68. Dorsal view; 69. Abdomen ventral view; 70. Posterior margins of terga; 71. Labrum; 72. Hypopharynx; 73. Left mandible; 74. Right mandible." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042544/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
); Gills II–VII without arched anal ribs (
<figureCitation box="[262,393,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 75–84" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,744,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-274@13.[151,1436,741,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 75–84. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 75. Maxilla; 76. Labium; 77. Dorsal surface of femur; 78. Foreleg; 79. Midleg; 80. Hindleg; 81. Claw; 82. Gill I; 83. Gill III; 84. Gill VII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042548/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="512">Figs 82–84</figureCitation>
). Cerci with row of hair-like setae dorsally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
