<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="513" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,150,393]" pageId="14" pageNumber="513">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,150,176]" pageId="14" pageNumber="513">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Braasch" authorityYear="1981" box="[329,505,150,176]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="513" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gilliesi">
<emphasis box="[329,505,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="513">Epeorus gilliesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from closely related species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sivaruban, Venkataraman &amp; Sivaramakrishnan" authorityYear="2013" box="[1057,1162,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="513" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petersi">
<emphasis box="[1057,1162,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="513">E. petersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: in larva (i) abdominal terga III–VIII with pair of brown spot (
<figureCitation box="[1058,1188,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,183,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[157,1429,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 68–74. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 68. Dorsal view; 69. Abdomen ventral view; 70. Posterior margins of terga; 71. Labrum; 72. Hypopharynx; 73. Left mandible; 74. Right mandible." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042544/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="513">Figs 68–70</figureCitation>
); (ii) a row of spine on posterior margin of segment I–X (
<figureCitation box="[530,661,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,183,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[157,1429,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 68–74. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 68. Dorsal view; 69. Abdomen ventral view; 70. Posterior margins of terga; 71. Labrum; 72. Hypopharynx; 73. Left mandible; 74. Right mandible." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042544/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="513">Figs 68–70</figureCitation>
); (iii) posterior edge of the gill 1 elongated (
<figureCitation box="[1152,1236,222,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 75–84" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,744,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-274@13.[151,1436,741,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 75–84. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 75. Maxilla; 76. Labium; 77. Dorsal surface of femur; 78. Foreleg; 79. Midleg; 80. Hindleg; 81. Claw; 82. Gill I; 83. Gill III; 84. Gill VII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042548/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="513">Fig. 82</figureCitation>
); and (iv) anterior margin of labrum with 14–15 denticles (
<figureCitation box="[602,686,258,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,183,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[157,1429,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 68–74. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) gilliesi 68. Dorsal view; 69. Abdomen ventral view; 70. Posterior margins of terga; 71. Labrum; 72. Hypopharynx; 73. Left mandible; 74. Right mandible." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042544/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="513">Fig. 71</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
